messages.content:
Here's a simple HTML file containing a slot machine simulator with the required features. The simulator will display three columns of symbols that spin upon page load and establish a WebSocket connection to the specified IRC server.

You can copy and paste the following code into a `.html` file and open it in a web browser:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Slot Machine Simulator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            background-color: #222;
            color: #fff;
        }
        #slots {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            font-size: 5rem;
            opacity: 0;
            transition: opacity 1s;
        }
        #spin {
            margin-top: 20px;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            cursor: pointer;
            background-color: #f39c12;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            color: white;
        }
        #spin:hover {
            background-color: #e67e22;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div id="slots"></div>
<button id="spin">Spin Again</button>

<script>
    const symbols = ["üçí", "üçã", "üçâ", "‚≠ê", "üîî", "üçá"];
    const slotsDiv = document.getElementById('slots');

    function spin() {
        let slots = [];
        for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
            const randomSymbol = symbols[Math.floor(Math.random() * symbols.length)];
            slots.push(randomSymbol);
        }
        slotsDiv.innerHTML = slots.join(' ');
        slotsDiv.style.opacity = 1; // Fade in
    }

    function connectWebSocket() {
        const randomNick = `casino_${Math.floor(Math.random() * 1000)}`;
        const ws = new WebSocket('wss://irc.h4ks.com:8097');

        ws.onopen = () => {
            console.log('Connected to IRC');
            ws.send(`NICK ${randomNick}`);
            ws.send('USER ' + randomNick + ' 0 * :WebSocket IRChat');
            ws.send('PRIVMSG _cloudbot :Hello from the Slot Machine Simulator!');
        };

        ws.onmessage = (event) => {
            console.log('Message from server:', event.data);
        };

        ws.onclose = () => {
            console.log('Disconnected from IRC');
        };

        ws.onerror = (error) => {
            console.error('WebSocket Error:', error);
        };
    }

    window.onload = () => {
        spin();
        connectWebSocket();
    };

    document.getElementById('spin').addEventListener('click', () => {
        slotsDiv.style.opacity = 0; // Fade out
        setTimeout(() => {
            spin();
        }, 1000); // Wait for fade out before spinning again
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How it Works:
- **Slot Machine**: The symbols are displayed in three columns. Upon page load, the slot machine spins, showing a random combination of symbols.
- **WebSocket Connection**: On connecting to the IRC server, the code sends several commands such as setting the nickname and sending a private message to "_cloudbot".
- **Interactive Spin**: The spin button allows users to spin the slot machine again.

### Notes:
1. This code establishes a WebSocket connection to `wss://irc.h4ks.com:8097`, which requires the server to be running and accessible for this to work correctly.
2. Ensure your browser allows WebSocket connections to this URL.
3. This simulation doesn't include rigorous error handling or user interface enhancements, as it serves as a basic proof of concept.
